description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for x2 Band 7 Deputy Network Accountants to join the Finance team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Deputy Network Accountant is an essential role within the Mental Health Finance Department. It will support the Network Accountant to provide a comprehensive budgetary control, financial planning and advisory service to Mental Health services and budget holders. The role will require effective and efficient reporting to enable the achievement of financial balance, and to participate in the business planning process and service developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The second Band 7 post will initially support the Head of Financial Management, working with the transition to the new locality model as well as other programmes of work. This role will eventually align to one of the locality finance teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated, flexible and organised individuals who are CCAB qualified (or have equivalent experience working at this level). Previous NHS management accounts experience is essential, as is experience of working with clinical budget holders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Saki Iqbal (Network Accountant) on 07950 886211 or email saki.iqbal@lscft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
